---
id: {{id}}
type: std_area
status: {{status}}
owner: {{owner}}
version: {{version}}
# Which charter goals this area addresses (ARCH-G<n> ids). An area that
# addresses no goal is an orphan — every area must point at >= 1 charter goal.
arch_goals: {{arch_goals}}
# Rule-groups and their rules are declared inline (flat layout): one area file
# per standard area. Rule-group ids follow STD-<AREA>-RG<n>; rule ids follow
# STD-<AREA>-RG<n>-R<n>.
rule_groups:
  - id: {{rule_group_id}}
    title: {{rule_group_title}}
    status: {{status}}
    owner: {{owner}}
    rules:
      - id: {{rule_id}}
        title: {{rule_title}}
        status: {{status}}
        # compliance_checks is the standards equivalent of acceptance criteria:
        # the deterministic statements that make this rule verifiable.
        compliance_checks: {{compliance_checks}}
        # Optional: other rule ids this rule depends on (depends_on: [STD-...]).
---

# {{title}}

What this standard area governs, and why. Each rule below states a single,
checkable expectation; the compliance_checks are how a reviewer or a gate
confirms a service meets it.
